      }
    },
    "image_with_text_FAfVaW": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_tfc8jA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q: </strong>We love that food and nostalgia are recurring themes in your work. Is there a particular memory or dish that always finds its way back in?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Ah, that’s a hard one - there’s so many! I think we all crave nostalgia. In 2019, I spent 3 months in Japan, mostly in Osaka where a lot of my relatives still live. I would often visit my grandma and every single time she would have snacks and mugicha on a beautiful lacquer tray ready for me when I arrived. It can be hard to communicate with my broken Japanese, so those acts of love were made even more meaningful. </p><p><strong>Q:</strong> What was your favourite childhood snack?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> Shrimp crackers! There’s two specific kinds I loved (and still love!)</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
